         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>721</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they will approve of giving gift[s] ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he brought water to the <hi>Preta</hi>s, [and] with both hands in <hi>añjali</hi> ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... compassionate one. The Buddha ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... may we obtain ... Towards the belly ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having approved ... with the alms-bowl they begged (?) from the water ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... by the sight of all <hi>Preta</hi>s ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the Buddha, the teacher, (with) a resounding, lovely (voice) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Now at the same time also water from the Gaṅgā river ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Thus the water dried up ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Without choice neither now ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>133</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... from the (rivers?) the <hi>Nāga</hi>s went (?) to the ocean.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Just now in that way ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment"><distinct type="ms_text">n_t\</distinct>: akṣara added later; addition marked with a cross above the line.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment"><hi>klanoṃtsāṃ ciñcä(ryāṃ)</hi>: cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a313"/> a5 <hi>klanoṃntsāṃ ciñcäryāṃ brahmaswar waśenyo</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment"><distinct type="ms_text">gaṅ_k\</distinct>: akṣaras added later; addition marked with a cross above the line.</note><note corresp="#b6" type="philcomment"><hi>mänt wäknā</hi>: probably followed by an elaboration in verse.</note></p>
         </div>
